0it%20to%20cut%20through%20%26quot%3Bbusywork.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicole%20Rivera-Reyes%2C%20a%20senior%20legal%20studies%20major%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Central%20Florida%2C%20said%20she%20avoids%20ChatGPT%20but%20relies%20heavily%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-notebooklm-audio-overviews-ai-podcast-tool-2024-01%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20NotebookLM%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20particularly%20to%20help%20her%20transcribe%20videos%20and%20take%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20at%20the%20most%2C%20it%20should%20be%20used%20to%20streamline%20a%20task%2C%20not%20completely%20do%20it%20over%2C%26quot%3B%20Rivera-Reyes%20said.%20%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20like%20%E2%80%94%20I%20understand%20the%20human%20element%20as%20far%20as%20error%20goes%2C%20right%2C%20but%20at%20most%2C%20I%20think%20it%20should%20be%20used%20to%20get%20through%20whatever%20busywork%20you%20have.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESamantha%20Wilson%2C%20a%20music%20education%20major%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Bridgeport%20in%20Connecticut%2C%20said%20she%20avoids%20AI%20altogether%20because%20she's%20%26quot%3Bterrified%26quot%3B%20of%20getting%20flagged%20for%20plagiarism.%20For%20her%20peers%20who%20do%20dare%2C%20Wilson%20said%20it's%20just%20a%20matter%20of%20sorting%20out%20the%20work%20that%20they%20find%20valuable%2C%20or%20critical%20to%20the%20learning%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20had%20classmates%20tell%20me%20that%20they%20use%20it%20for%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20Wilson%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20think%20that%20they're%20just%20utilizing%20the%20tool%20because%20they%20feel%20like%20the%20essay%20is%20a%20waste%20of%20their%20time.%20They%20already%20know%20the%20material%2C%20and%20they'd%20be%20fine%20not%20getting%20that%20experience%20of%20writing%20the%20paper.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221b68f89b-ce4c-422c-b3ae-80578cbc8744%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOthers%20are%20turning%20to%20AI%20to%20cope%20with%20what%20they%20describe%20as%20overwhelming%20course%20loads%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20health%20sciences%20major%20and%20a%20musical%20theater%20student%20are%20both%20wrapping%20up%20their%20final%20years%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Miami.%20Both%2C%20who%20requested%20anonymity%20to%20avoid%20academic%20consequences%2C%20said%20they're%20relatively%20heavy%20AI%20users%20and%20cited%20similar%20reasons%20%E2%80%94%20heavy%20loads%20and%20teachers%20who%20moved%20faster%20than%20they%20felt%20they%20could%20keep%20up%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20a%20teacher%20who%20was%20moving%20incredibly%20fast%2C%20and%20I%20barely%20even%20understood%20any%20of%20the%20concepts%2C%20and%20at%20that%20point%2C%20it%20was%20just%20like%20I%20needed%20to%20get%20a%20good%20grade%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20musical%20theater%20student%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BAI%20broke%20down%20the%20concepts%20in%20a%20way%20that%20made%20it%20easier%20to%20understand%20for%20me%20than%20the%20actual%20teacher.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20theater%20student%20said%20the%20process%20felt%20mercenary%2C%20like%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bjust%20checking%20a%20box%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20that%20balancing%20her%20stacked%20schedule%20would%20become%20impossible%20without%20AI%20to%20clear%20quick%20tasks%20off%20her%20plate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20my%20classes%2C%20on%20top%20of%20a%20show%20that%20I%20produce%2C%20on%20top%20of%20work%20hours%2C%20on%20top%20of%20potentially%20designing%20for%20another%20show%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20not%20have%20time.%20If%20I%20couldn't%20get%20through%20my%20homework%20quickly%2C%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20I%20would%20do.%20I%20already%20struggle%20enough%20to%20take%20care%20of%20myself%20in%20the%20busiest%20times.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20health%20sciences%20major%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewho%20said%20she%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eused%20AI%20to%20get%20through%20a%20physics%20course%20in%20a%20similar%20fashion%2C%20said%20the%20tool%20is%20vital%20in%20freeing%20up%20her%20time%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20for%20social%20needs%20but%20for%20self-care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20time%20I%20get%20back%20by%20using%20AI%2C%20I%20honestly%20just%20use%20to%20shower%20and%20sleep.%20In%20sophomore%20year%20before%20I%20used%20any%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20so%20bad%2C%20but%20I%20used%20to%20have%20like%20zero%20food%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BNow%20I'm%20actually%20able%20to%20take%20care%20of%20basic%20human%20needs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudents%20turning%20to%20AI%20to%20bail%20them%20out%20isn't%20unique%20to%20a%20single%20university.%20An%20architectural%20engineering%20student%20at%20Farmingdale%20State%20College%20in%20New%20York%20said%20he%20depended%20on%20it%20to%20save%20his%20grade%20in%20a%20challenging%20statics%20course.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20student%2C%20who%20requested%20anonymity%20given%20his%20use%20of%20AI%2C%20felt%20his%20entire%20class%20had%20fallen%20behind%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20semester.%20He%20said%20it%20prompted%20an%20incident%20of%20covert%20cheating%20%E2%80%94%20during%20a%20final%20conducted%20on%20university%20grounds%2C%20the%20student%20described%20a%20group%20effort%20to%20source%20and%20share%20answers%20to%20test%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNone%20of%20us%20were%20retaining%20any%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20what%20we%20did%20was%20sort%20of%20like%20a%20group%20chat%20where%20half%20of%20us%20used%20Chegg%20and%20the%20other%20half%20used%20ChatGPT%2C%20and%20we%20shared%20answers%20for%20the%20test.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b1d5098f-54d4-4423-a7ad-e53149d63b55%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20students%20fear%20the%20consequences%20of%20long-term%20reliance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20students%20told%20BI%20that%20they%20worried%20that%2C%20for%20all%20its%20time-saving%20and%20revision%20benefits%2C%20using%20AI%20would%20come%20at%20a%20critical%20cost%20%E2%80%94%20skill%20atrophy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERiley%2C%20a%20computer%20science%20major%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Florida%20who%20requested%20to%20go%20by%20his%20first%20name%2C%20said%20he's%20already%20seeing%20the%20effects%20of%20long-term%20AI%20usage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20will%20be%20the%20first%20one%20to%20tell%20you%20I've%20struggled%20with%20that%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20Riley%20said.%20%26quot%3BWith%20using%20AI%20for%20something%20and%20then%20going%20back%20to%20it%2C%20like%2C%20a%20month%20later%2C%20and%20being%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20I%20don't%20remember%20what%20this%20does%2C%20or%20I%20don't%20remember%20how%20I%20did%20this.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20paper%20released%20by%20researchers%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.404media.co%2Fmicrosoft-study-finds-ai-makes-human-cognition-atrophied-and-unprepared-3%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%20and%20Carnegie%20Mellon%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggested%20that%20the%20more%20workers%20relied%20on%20AI%20to%20automate%20tedious%20tasks%2C%20the%20more%20detached%20from%20the%20output%20they%20became.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSurprisingly%2C%20while%20AI%20can%20improve%20efficiency%2C%20it%20may%20also%20reduce%20critical%20engagement%2C%20particularly%20in%20routine%20or%20lower-stakes%20tasks%20in%20which%20users%20simply%20rely%20on%20AI%2C%20raising%20concerns%20about%20long-term%20reliance%20and%20diminished%20independent%20problem-solving%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20added%20that%20data%20showed%20a%20%26quot%3Bshift%20in%20cognitive%20effort%26quot%3B%20as%20knowledge%20workers%20moved%20from%20completing%20tasks%20themselves%20to%20overseeing%20the%20completion%20of%20tasks%20by%20generative%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20used%20%26quot%3Bimproperly%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20asserted%20that%20technologies%20could%20mean%20the%20%26quot%3Bdeterioration%20of%20cognitive%20faculties.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20key%20irony%20of%20automation%20is%20that%20by%20mechanizing%20routine%20tasks%20and%20leaving%20exception-handling%20to%20the%20human%20user%2C%20you%20deprive%20the%20user%20of%20the%20routine%20opportunities%20to%20practice%20their%20judgment%20and%20strengthen%20their%20cognitive%20musculature%2C%20leaving%20them%20atrophied%20and%20unprepared%20when%20the%20exceptions%20do%20arise%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20up%20to%20the%20individual%2C%20said%20Patrick%20Wilson%2C%20an%20anthropology%20student%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Hawai'i%20at%20M%C4%81noa%2C%20to%20bridle%20the%20tech%20in%20a%20way%20that%20works%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20such%20an%20incredibly%20useful%20tool%2C%20it's%20really%20hard%20to%20just%20dismiss%20it%20based%20over%20that%20one%20concern%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20kind%20of%20on%20us%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20we're%20still%20being%20critical%2C%20and%20maintaining%20our%20abilities.%20But%20if%20I%20think%2C%20if%20you're%20using%20it%20well%2C%20if%20you're%20really%20using%20it%20to%20its%20full%20potential%2C%20then%2C%20by%20definition%2C%20you're%20doing%20a%20lot%20of%20critical%20thinking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Keon%2C%20who%20studies%20finance%20at%20Saint%20Joseph's%20University%20in%20Philadelphia%2C%20said%20that%20AI%20is%20a%20natural%20next%20step%20in%20technological%20evolution%20and%20that%20the%20further%20automation%20of%20human%20tasks%20seems%20inevitable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20reliant%20on%20this%20stuff%2C%20but%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20isn't%20that%20kind%20of%20like%2C%20what%20technologies%2C%20like%20%E2%80%94%20sort%20of%20the%20general%20idea%20is%2C%20it's%20designed%20to%20improve%20and%20handle%20functions%20that%20otherwise%20would%20take%2C%20you%20know%2C%20manpower%20or%20horsepower%2C%20or%20labor%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Keon%20distinguishes%20between%20academic%20and%20professional%20settings.%20He%20said%20that%20a%20boost%20from%20AI%20might%20be%20a%20good%20thing%20when%20you're%20in%20the%20work%20force%2C%20but%20that%20automating%20your%20work%20while%20still%20in%20university%20could%20prove%20detrimental.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20a%20productivity%20standpoint%2C%20if%20you're%20in%20a%20company%2C%20then%2C%20yeah%2C%20that's%20a%20great%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20Keon%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20you're%20in%20an%20academic%20setting%2C%20if%20you're%20in%20a%20creative%20setting%2C%20I%20think%20that%20boredom%20and%20that%20brainstorm%20is%20a%20very%20crucial%20part%20of%20any%20kind%20of%20idea-generating%20creativity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-college-students-use-ai-homework-study-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742986621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67e3269563d72727e1983c85%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-college-students-use-ai-homework-study-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Conversations%20with%20over%20a%20dozen%20college%20students%20across%20the%20US%20revealed%20fears%20of%20developing%20an%20over-reliance%20on%20AI.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sperkel%40insider.com%20(Sarah%20Perkel)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-college-students-use-ai-homework-study-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russia%20says%20sanctions%20must%20be%20lifted%20before%20Ukraine%20maritime%20ceasefire%20can%20start%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742986329000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F6212%2Flive%2F350a26