as%20my%20husband's%20was%20white%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20need%20to%20own%20my%20blackness.%20This%20is%20a%20post%20I%20made%20today%20morning%2C%20and%20then%20deleted%20because%20I%20was%20flustered%20by%20the%20flurry%20of%20responses.%20I%20am%20reposting%20it%20because%20certain%20well%20wishers%20said%20that%20there%20were%20things%20there%20that%20needed%20to%20be%20discussed.%20I%20agree.%20So%20here%20goes%2C%20once%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20senior%20officer%20wrote%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Brelentless%20parade%20of%20comparisons%26quot%3B%20with%20her%20husband%20ever%20since%20she%20took%20over.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20about%20being%20labelled%20black%20(with%20that%20quiet%20sub%20text%20of%20being%20woman)%2C%20as%20if%20that%20were%20something%20to%20be%20desperately%20ashamed%20of.%20Black%20is%20as%20black%20does.%20Not%20just%20black%20the%20colour%2C%20but%20black%20the%20ne'er%20do%20good%2C%20black%20the%20malaise%2C%20the%20cold%20despotism%2C%20the%20heart%20of%20darkness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20why%20should%20black%20be%20vilified%3F%20Black%20is%20the%20all%20pervasive%20truth%20of%20the%20universe.%20Black%20is%20that%20which%20can%20absorb%20anything%2C%20the%20most%20powerful%20pulse%20of%20energy%20known%20to%20humankind.%20It%20is%20the%20colour%20that%20works%20on%20everyone%2C%20the%20dress%20code%20for%20office%2C%20the%20lustre%20of%20evening%20wear%2C%20the%20essence%20of%20kajol%2C%20the%20promise%20of%20rain%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Muraleedharan%20wrote%20of%20her%20childhood%20insecurity%20over%20her%20complexion.%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20four%20year%20old%20I%20apparently%20asked%20my%20mother%20whether%20she%20could%20put%20me%20back%20in%20her%20womb%20and%20bring%20me%20out%20again%2C%20all%20white%20and%20pretty.%20I%20have%20lived%20for%20over%2050%20years%20buried%20under%20that%20narrative%20of%20not%20being%20a%20colour%20that%20was%20good%20enough.%20And%20buying%20into%20that%20narrative.%20Of%20not%20seeing%20beauty%20or%20value%20in%20black.%20Of%20being%20fascinated%20by%20fair%20skin.%20And%20fair%20minds%2C%20and%20all%20that%20was%20fair%20and%20good%20and%20wholesome.%20And%20of%20feeling%20that%20I%20was%20a%20lesser%20person%20for%20not%20being%20that%20which%20had%20to%20be%20compensated%20somehow%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTill%20my%20children.%20Who%20gloried%20in%20their%20black%20heritage.%20Who%20kept%20finding%20beauty%20where%20I%20noticed%20none.%20Who%20thought%20that%20black%20was%20awesome.%20Who%20helped%20me%20see.%20That%20black%20is%20beautiful.%20That%20black%20is%20gorgeousness.%20That%20I%20dig%20black%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20senior%20bureaucrat's%20brave%20words%20have%20drawn%20appreciation%20from%20across%20the%20spectrum.%20Among%20the%20ones%20who%20praised%20Ms%20Muraleedharan%20is%20VD%20Satheesan%2C%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20in%20the%20Kerala%20Assembly.%20Mr%20Satheesan%20wrote%20that%20every%20word%20in%20her%20post%20is%20%26quot%3Bheart-touching%26quot%3B.%20He%20also%20said%20his%20mother%20had%20a%20dark%20complexion%20and%20that%20this%20issue%20must%20be%20discussed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Muraleedharan%20has%20earlier%20served%20in%20key%20roles%2C%20including%20as%20Director%20General%2C%20National%20Institute%20Of%20Fashion%20Technology%2C%20at%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Panchayati%20Raj%2C%20as%20COO%20at%20National%20Rural%20Livelihoods%20Mission%20and%20as%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Kudumbashree%20mission.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20ANI%20later%2C%20the%20top%20officer%20said%20the%20coloured%20comment%20that%20prompted%20her%20long%20post%20was%20probably%20made%20in%20a%20humourous%20manner.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20thing%20is%2C%20behind%20the%20humour%2C%20there%20is%20an%20entire%20value%20connotation%20and%20that%20value%20connotation%20is%20that%20the%20kind%20of%20administration%20that%20I%20do%20is%20black%20and%20the%20connotation%20is%20that%20because%20it%20is%20black%2C%20it%20is%20not%20good%2C%20and%20there%20was%20something%20wrong%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20wrong%20about%20black%3F%20Isn't%20it%20more%20a%20perception%20than%20a%20reality%3F%20It%20is%20important%20to%20claim%20blackness%20as%20something%20which%20is%20worthwhile%20and%20beautiful...I%20think%20it's%20high%20time%20for%20me%20not%20to%20feel%20defensive%20about%20either%20the%20fact%20that%20I%20am%20a%20woman%20or%20that%20I%20am%20dark.%20It's%20time%20that%20I%20own%20both%20of%20these%20and%20that%20I%20come%20out%20strongly.%20By%20my%20coming%20out%20strongly%2C%20maybe%20it%20will%20help%20those%20people%20who%20are%20going%20through%20similar%20feelings%20of%20insecurity%20and%20inadequacy%2C%20to%20feel%20that%20we%20are%20worth%20it%20and%20we%20don't%20need%20external%20validation%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742985840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fe36n7qs8_kerala-chief-secy_625x300_26_March_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsarada-muraleedharan-i-dig-black-kerala-bureaucrat-calls-out-colourism-comparison-to-husband-8013990%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sarada%20Muraleedharan%2C%20Kerala's%20Chief%20Secretary%2C%20has%20hit%20out%20at%20social%20media%20users%20ridiculing%20her%20for%20her%20dark%20complexion%20and%20colorist%20barbs%20comparing%20her%20work%20with%20that%20of%20her%20husband%20--%20former%20Kerala%20Chief%20Secretary%20V%20Venu%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sonakshi%20on%20posting%20pics%20with%20Zaheer%3A%20We%20are%20happy%20to%20share%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742985799000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2