rs%20will%20benefit%20from%20the%20pay%20revision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Is%20Pay%20Commission%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPay%20Commission%20is%20a%20government-appointed%20body%20that%20reviews%20and%20recommends%20salary%2C%20pension%2C%20and%20benefits%20revisions%20for%20central%20government%20employees%20and%20pensioners%20in%20India.%20It%20is%20set%20up%20periodically%20(usually%20every%2010%20years)%20to%20revise%20pay%20scales%20based%20on%20economic%20conditions%2C%20inflation%2C%20and%20cost%20of%20living.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEstimated%20Salary%20Increase%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20a%20mid-level%20government%20employee%20earns%20an%20average%20of%20Rs%201%20lakh%20per%20month%20(pre-tax).%20Based%20on%20different%20budget%20allocations%2C%20the%20expected%20salary%20increase%20could%20be%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWith%20Rs%201.75%20lakh%20crore%20allocation%20-%20Salary%20may%20rise%20to%20Rs%201%2C14%2C600%20per%20month.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWith%20Rs%202%20lakh%20crore%20allocation%20-%20Salary%20may%20grow%20to%20Rs%201%2C16%2C700%20per%20month.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWith%20a%20Rs%202.25%20lakh%20crore%20allocation%20-%20Salary%20may%20increase%20to%20Rs%201%2C18%2C800%20per%20month.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20Will%20The%20Pay%20Hike%20Take%20Effect%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20has%20been%20no%20official%20announcement%20about%20the%20formation%20of%20the%208th%20Pay%20Commission%2C%20experts%20believe%20the%20government%20may%20constitute%20the%20panel%20in%20April%202025%2C%20with%20its%20recommendations%20coming%20into%20effect%20by%202026%20or%202027.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20It's%20Different%20From%20The%207th%20Pay%20Commission%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%207th%20Pay%20Commission%20was%20implemented%20in%202016%2C%20costing%20the%20government%20Rs%201.02%20lakh%20crore.%20It%20revised%20salaries%20and%20pensions%20rolled%20out%20from%20July%202016%2C%20though%20implemented%20retrospectively%20from%20January%202016.%20The%20financial%20impact%20was%20absorbed%20in%20FY%202016-17.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fitment%20factor%20(used%20to%20calculate%20salary%20hikes)%20was%20increased%20by%202.57%20times%2C%20raising%20the%20minimum%20basic%20salary%20from%20Rs%207%2C000%20to%20Rs%2018%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20if%20the%208th%20Pay%20Commission%20increases%20the%20fitment%20factor%20to%203%20or%20more%2C%20government%20employees%20can%20expect%20a%20substantial%20salary%20hike.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20formed%2C%20the%208th%20Pay%20Commission%20will%20consult%20employee%20unions%20and%20other%20stakeholders%20to%20decide%20the%20fitment%20factor%20and%20salary%20revisions.%20Unions%20are%20expected%20to%20demand%20a%20fitment%20factor%20of%202.57%20or%20higher%2C%20similar%20to%20the%207th%20Pay%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Finance%20Secretary%20Subhash%20Chandra%20Garg%20suggested%20in%20January%20that%20this%20might%20be%20unrealistic%2C%20predicting%20a%20fitment%20factor%20closer%20to%201.92.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742983200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2F6k6p2298_money-generic_625x300_15_February_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F8th-pay-commission-government-staff-may-get-rs-14-000-19-000-salary-hike-8014474%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20salaries%20of%20central%20government%20employees%20may%20rise%20by%20up%20to%20Rs%2019%2C000%20per%20month%20if%20the%208th%20Pay%20Commission%20is%20implemented%2C%20Goldman%20Sachs%20has%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F8th-pay-commission-government-staff-may-get-rs-14-000-19-000-salary-hike-8014474%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%229%20weird%20recession%20indicators%