t%20in%20the%201970s%2C%20skirts%20got%20longer%20again%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2021-08-27%2Ffashion-trends-after-pandemic-debunk-hemline-index-return-to-glamour%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eas%20Bloomberg%20reported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20in%20early%202022%2C%20the%20ultra-mini%20skirt%2C%20also%20called%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktoker-viral-diesel-micro-miniskirt-review-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20micro%20mini%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20the%20%26quot%3Bit%26quot%3B%20item%20before%20inflation%20rose%20and%20the%20ankle-length%20maxi%20skirt%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-brands-trends-they-brought-back-made-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ein%20vogue%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2236425bb9-dd73-4707-9fac-59901ef46d9f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECardboard%20box%20indicator%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thinking%20goes%20that%20cardboard%20boxes%20can%20act%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Fstory%2F2022-12-22%2Fworld-cardboard-boxes-bad-sign-economy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20barometer%20for%20the%20health%20of%20the%20economy%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20they%20play%20such%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20transporting%20goods%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20to%20consumers%20who%20buy%20things%20online%2C%20but%20to%20stores%20and%20warehouses%20that%20receive%20those%20goods%20in%20bulk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20that%20if%20demand%20for%20cardboard%20is%20slowing%2C%20consumers%20are%20buying%20less%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20indicator%20may%20be%20more%20accurate%20than%20some%20of%20the%20others%2C%20as%20there's%20such%20a%20direct%20correlation%20between%20cardboard%20demand%20and%20consumer%20purchasing.%20Back%20in%20early%202009%2C%20as%20the%20US%20was%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20recession%2C%20cardboard%20shipments%20declined%20drastically%20and%20US%20cardboard%20manufacturers'%20operating%20rates%20dipped%20as%20well.%20A%20similar%20trend%20arose%20in%20early%202023%3A%20the%20Fibre%20Box%20Association%2C%20a%20trade%20group%20that%20represents%20the%20industry%2C%20reported%20that%20cardboard%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Frecession-warning-cardboard-demand-economy-2008-financial-crisis-ecommerce-shipping-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eshipments%20had%20fallen%208.4%25%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20of%202022%2C%20the%20steepest%20decline%20since%20the%20financial%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c5d32931-cd51-44cb-80d7-a5566045967f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDiaper%20rash%20indicator%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDiapering%20a%20baby%20is%20a%20costly%20endeavor%20for%20parents%20%E2%80%94%20to%20the%20tune%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.parents.com%2Fparenting%2Fmoney%2Fsaving%2Fsave-money-and-build-a-diaper-stockpile%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%24500%20to%20%24900%20annually%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20during%20economic%20hard%20times%2C%20some%20parents%20may%20be%20forced%20to%20ration%20diapers%20to%20save%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20you%20change%20a%20baby's%20diaper%20less%20frequently%2C%20there's%20a%20higher%20chance%20the%20baby%20will%20develop%20diaper%20rash%2C%20leading%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-diaper-rash-economic-indicator-2011-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eincreased%20sales%20of%20ointment%20to%20treat%20it%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20lower%20diaper%20sales%20and%20higher%20ointment%20sales%20can%20serve%20as%20a%20clue%20that%20the%20economy%20is%20contracting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20examples%20of%20this%20indicator%20coming%20into%20play%20during%20periods%20of%20belt-tightening.%20The%20trend%20began%20during%20tough%20economic%20times%20in%202011%2C%20when%20parents%20cut%20back%20on%20buying%20diapers%20or%20traded%20down%20to%20cheaper%20brands%20at%20the%20same%20time%20that%20ointment%20sales%20rose%208%25%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2FSB10001424052970203791904576609254230522240%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20reported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20index%20isn't%20airtight%3A%20the%20birth%20rate%20was%20declining%20around%20the%20same%20time%2C%20diaper%20technology%20improved%20to%20show%20parents%20whether%20a%20diaper%20was%20wet%20or%20not%2C%20and%20parents%20had%20begun%20potty%20training%20earlier%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20cut%20costs%2C%20the%20Journal%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2290ffdcb6-f0ae-4218-92b3-f035892102cb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Champagne%20index%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Champagne%20index%20is%20basically%20the%20inverse%20of%20the%20lipstick%20index%3A%20when%20the%20economy%20is%20bad%2C%20people%20will%20stop%20buying%20as%20much%20Champagne%20and%20opt%20for%20cheaper%20alcohol%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20played%20out%20before.%20Prior%20to%20the%202008%20recession%2C%20US%20sales%20of%20Champagne%20surpassed%2023%20million%20bottles%2C%20but%20by%202009%2C%20that%20number%20had%20dipped%20to%2012.5%20million%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbusinessreview.berkeley.edu%2Feconomic-indicators-lipstick-and-underwear%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eaccording%20to%20UC%20Berkeley's%20Business%20Review%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20index%20may%20be%20more%20closely%20tied%20to%20societal%20sentiment%20more%20broadly%2C%20however%2C%20since%20fewer%20celebrations%20means%20fewer%20occasions%20for%20bubbly.%20Indeed%2C%20Champagne%20sales%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchampagne-sales-decline-during-coronavirus-pandemic-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edropped%2018%25%20by%20volume%20in%202020%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20CIVC%2C%20a%20champagne%20industry%20trade%20group%2C%20reported%20at%20the%20time.%20Then%2C%20in%202021%2C%20as%20travel%20and%20socializing%20began%20to%20resume%2C%20sales%20of%20Champagne%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-years-champagne-swapped-for-cheaper-prosecco-amid-economic-uncertainty-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereached%20a%20record%20high%20of%20%245.7%20billion%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2014%25%20higher%20than%20the%20pre-pandemic%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229b3867ce-4d1e-4e2b-8fdd-cc1f5c08a572%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20stripper%20index%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EExotic%20dancers%20are%20often%20among%20the%20first%20group%20of%20people%20to%20warn%20of%20a%20coming%20recession%2C%20Aaliyah%20Kissick%2C%20CEO%20of%20Financial%20Literacy%20Diaries%20and%20a%20Gen%20Z%20money%20expert%2C%20told%20BI%20last%20year.%20That%20lends%20credence%20to%20another%20predictive%20theory%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheface.com%2Fsociety%2Fstrippers-recession-stripping-adult-industry-porn-politics-economy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20Stripper%20Index.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKissick%20pointed%20to%20strippers'%20tips%20as%20a%20microcosm%20for%20elastic%20goods.%20The%20elasticity%20of%20a%20product%20refers%20to%20how%20changing%20prices%20may%20or%20may%20not%20trigger%20changing%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoffee%2C%20for%20example%2C%20is%20an%20inelastic%20good.%20Even%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoffee-prices-increases-inflation-drought-frost-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eprices%20rise%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20people%20continue%20to%20buy%20it%20because%20they%20just%20aren't%20willing%20to%20go%20without%20it.%20The%20fact%20that%20caffeine%20can%20be%20an%20addictive%20substance%20means%20people%20won't%20change%20their%20demand%20for%20coffee%20even%20in%20tough%20economic%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20where%20a%20typical%20white-collar%20worker%20isn't%20willing%20to%20forgo%20coffee%20during%20a%20recession%2C%20he%20may%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20ditch%20the%20after-hours%20entertainment%2C%20or%20he'll%20tip%20his%20performers%20less%2C%20Kissick%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20theory%20can%20more%20broadly%20be%20applied%20to%20any%20service%20industry%20that%20operates%20with%20a%20tipping%20culture%2C%20Peter%20C.%20Earle%2C%20senior%20economist%20at%20the%20American%20Institute%20for%20Economic%20Research%2C%20told%20BI%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20in%20the%20food%20service%20industry%20have%20noticed%20lately%2C%20a%20decrease%20in%20restaurant%20tipping%20suggests%20that%20consumers%20are%20reducing%20discretionary%20spending%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20because%20of%20rising%20unemployment%2C%20the%20debilitating%20effect%20of%20inflation%2C%20or%20both%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweird-recession-indicators%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742983142000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67e2d9c669253ccddf9a3d7d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweird-recession-indicators%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Less%20formal%20indicators%20of%20a%20recession%2C%20from%20lipstick%20sales