orkers%20think%20I%20was%20slacking%20off%20or%20that%20I%20wasn't%20as%20committed%20as%20I%20was%20before%20children%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomething%20surprising%20happened%3A%20My%20colleagues%20respected%20it.%20Not%20only%20that%2C%20but%20someone%20in%20another%20department%20told%20me%20she%20had%20always%20hesitated%20to%20shut%20down%20at%205%3A30%20p.m.%20because%20no%20one%20else%20did.%20When%20she%20saw%20me%20doing%20it%2C%20and%20openly%20explaining%20why%2C%20she%20felt%20empowered%20to%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ce27fdbb-7656-4f43-aa77-61950f99aa62%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20stopped%20apologizing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EParents%2C%20especially%20moms%2C%20are%20often%20expected%20to%20downplay%20or%20disengage%20with%20their%20caregiving%20responsibilities%20at%20work.%20I%20stopped%20doing%20that.%20Instead%20of%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20so%20sorry%2C%20I%20have%20to%20leave%20for%20nursery%20school%20pickup%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20now%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20a%20hard%20stop%20at%205%20p.m.%20because%20that's%20when%20my%20childcare%20ends.%26quot%3B%20No%20apology%2C%20no%20guilt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20shift%20reinforces%20the%20idea%20that%20family%20responsibilities%20are%20just%20as%20valid%20as%20work%20commitments%2C%20not%20just%20to%20my%20colleagues%20but%20to%20myself.%20And%20shocker%3A%20No%20one%20questions%20it.%20There%20might%20be%20some%20unstated%20frustration%20because%20meetings%20are%20challenging%20to%20schedule%2C%20but%20overall%2C%20everyone%20is%20pretty%20accepting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2213547cf9-f761-4b34-ab6e-4c9bf27aedc5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20started%20applying%20loud%20living%20at%20home%20too%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELoud%20living%20isn't%20just%20for%20work.%20It's%20for%20life.%20In%20addition%20to%20being%20open%20with%20my%20colleagues%2C%20I%20communicate%20more%20clearly%20with%20everyone%20in%20my%20life%20about%20what%20I%20need.%20Instead%20of%20