es%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fcommodities%2Foil-price%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECrude%20oil%20futures%3C%2Fa%3E%20rose%20about%201%25%20on%20the%20news.%20Global%20energy%20prices%20have%20been%20broadly%20depressed%20in%20recent%20months%20due%20to%20global%20growth%20concerns%20and%20ample%20supply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fc9330b9-8b99-4082-88e9-0de89d55dc43%5C%22%3EChina%20is%20a%20big%20market%20for%20Venezuela%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20tariffs%20are%20targeted%20at%20all%20countries%20that%20buy%20Venezuelan%20oil%2C%20analysts%20say%20they%20would%20most%20affect%20China%2C%20which%20accounted%20for%2055%25%20of%20the%20South%20American%20country's%20crude%20and%20fuel%20exports%20in%20February%2C%20according%20to%20Reuters%20estimates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVenezuelan%20oil%20is%20sanctioned%20by%20the%20US%2C%20so%20much%20of%20the%20energy%20trade%20passes%20through%20dark%20channels.%20Venezuela%20is%20not%20one%20of%20China's%20biggest%20sources%20of%20oil%20%E2%80%94%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20Russia%20are%20its%20top%20suppliers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20secondary%20tariffs%20are%20an%20indirect%20sanction%20to%20degrade%20Venezuela's%20oil%20supply%20capability%20and%20hurt%20China's%20teapot%20refining%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Mukesh%20Sahdev%2C%20the%20global%20head%20of%20commodity%20markets%20at%20research%20firm%20Rystad%20Energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESahdev%20said%20Chinese%20%26quot%3Bteapots%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20independent%20oil%20refiners%20in%20China%20%E2%80%94%20would%20struggle%20for%20crude%20oil%20supply%20and%20resort%20to%20stock%20drawdowns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShould%20the%20tariffs%20persist%20into%20the%20summer%20%E2%80%94%20when%20crude%20oil%20demand%20typically%20rises%20due%20to%20air%20cooling%20needs%20%E2%80%94%20prices%20of%20the%20commodity%20could%20get%20a%20further%20boost%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3