now%20a%20guy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20wide-open%20nature%20of%20the%20housing%20market%20has%20been%20breaking%20down%20for%20a%20while.%20Most%20real%20estate%20agents%20have%20traditionally%20taken%20a%20maximalist%20approach%20to%20marketing%20homes%2C%20sharing%20listings%20widely%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-agents-lawsuits-buy-sell-homes-forever-housing-market-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elocal%20databases%20known%20as%20multiple%20listing%20services%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Agents%20browse%20the%20MLS%20to%20get%20details%20on%20homes%20available%20for%20sale%2C%20while%20search%20portals%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-my-zestimate-accurate-home-prices-obsession-zillow-algorithm-homeowner-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZillow%3C%2Fa%3E%20pull%20the%20data%20onto%20their%20own%20websites%20for%20regular%20home%20shoppers%20to%20scroll%20through.%20The%20thinking%20is%20simple%3A%20More%20eyes%20on%20a%20listing%20means%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faustralia-real-estate-home-auctions-america-buy-sell-bidding-wars-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20potential%20bidders%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20giving%20a%20homeowner%20the%20best%20chance%20of%20selling%20quickly%20and%20lucratively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20model%20is%20even%20backstopped%20by%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors%2C%20a%20powerful%20industry%20group%20that%20sets%20the%20rules%20for%20most%20MLSes%20around%20the%20country.%20NAR%20instituted%20a%20rule%20in%202020%20known%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-fight-clear-cooperation-realtors-zillow-pocket-listings-homes-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclear%20cooperation%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20says%20that%20once%20a%20real%20estate%20agent%20starts%20marketing%20a%20home%20publicly%20%E2%80%94%20on%20a%20website%2C%20through%20an%20email%20blast%2C%20or%20even%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bfor%20sale%26quot%3B%20sign%20in%20the%20front%20yard%20%E2%80%94%20they%20must%20list%20it%20on%20the%20MLS%20within%20one%20day.%20The%20rule%20was%20meant%20to%20prevent%20freeloading%20and%20encourage%20participation%20in%20the%20MLS%2C%20keeping%20listings%20in%20one%20place%20for%20other%20agents%20and%20their%20clients%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20however%2C%20the%20clear%20cooperation%20rule%20has%20been%20challenged%20by%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20players%20in%20the%20game%2C%20who%20want%20to%20act%20as%20the%20new%20bouncers%20for%20VIP%20rooms%20filled%20with%20exclusive%20home%20listings.%20In%20particular%2C%20Compass%2C%20the%20country's%20largest%20real%20estate%20brokerage%20by%20sales%20volume%2C%20wants%20to%20take%20charge%20of%20the%20aforementioned%20velvet%20rope.%20Compass%20agents%20are%20increasingly%20hoarding%20their%20listings%20internally%2C%20shunning%20the%20MLS%20and%20making%20homes%20available%20only%20to%20buyers%20who%20work%20with%20other%20Compass%20agents.%20The%20company's%20founder%20and%20CEO%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompass-ipo-ceo-robert-reffkin-shares-wealth-net-worth-billionaire-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERobert%20Reffkin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20also%20been%20crusading%20against%20the%20clear%20cooperation%20policy.%20Reffkin%20argues%20that%20sellers%20should%20reject%20the%20one-size-fits-all%20approach%20of%20the%20MLS%20and%20exert%20more%20control%20over%20how%20their%20home%20is%20marketed.%20His%20campaign%20has%20stoked%20fierce%20infighting%20among%20real%20estate%20agents%20and%20raised%20a%20fundamental%20question%3A%20Who%20should%20be%20able%20to%20see%20the%20homes%20for%20sale%20in%20the%20US%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20the%20fight%20is%20ongoing.%20After%20months%20of%20debate%2C%20NAR%20said%20Tuesday%20it%20would%20leave%20the%20clear%20cooperation%20policy%20intact%20while%20adding%20another%20rule%20that%20functions%20as%20a%20small%20concession%20to%20Compass.%20The%20apparent%20attempt%20at%20compromise%20will%20probably%20end%20up%20pleasing%20no%20one.%20But%20while%20clear%20cooperation%20remains%20in%20place%20for%20now%2C%20the%20housing%20market%20continues%20to%20hurtle%20toward%20a%20decidedly%20%3Cem%3Eun%3C%2Fem%3Ecooperative%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20in%20favor%20of%20clear%20cooperation%20argue%20the%20rule%20is%20responsible%20for%20America's%20uniquely%20transparent%20housing%20market%20%E2%80%94%20the%20reason%20you%20can%20hop%20on%20Zillow%20or%20Realtor.com%20and%20get%20the%20lay%20of%20the%20land.%20The%20policy%20was%20supposed%20to%20stem%20the%20rise%20of%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bpocket%20listings%2C%26quot%3B%20homes%20marketed%20for%20sale%20but%20unavailable%20on%20the%20MLS.%20If%20agents%20stop%20contributing%20listings%20to%20the%20shared%20databases%2C%20many%20in%20the%20industry%20warn%2C%20a%20once%20unified%20housing%20market%20could%20break%20up%20into%20silos%2C%20with%20home%20listings%20distributed%20among%20clubby%20groups%20of%20brokers%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bprivate%20listing%20networks%26quot%3B%20or%20gatekept%20within%20brokerages%20like%20Compass.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20world%2C%20some%20agents%20will%20have%20access%20to%20a%20lot%20more%20properties%20than%20others.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbad-real-estate-agents-realtors-homebuyers-sellers-housing-market-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPick%20the%20wrong%20rep%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20you%20could%20unknowingly%20miss%20out%20on%20your%20dream%20home.%20And%20while%20there%20are%20good%20reasons%20someone%20might%20not%20want%20their%20house%20touted%20on%20the%20MLS%20%E2%80%94%20a%20celebrity%20like%20Brad%20Pitt%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20probably%20doesn't%20want%20their%20business%20aired%20out%20for%20everyone%20to%20see%20%E2%80%94%20conventional%20wisdom%20says%20sharing%20a%20home%20widely%20is%20the%20best%20way%20to%20get%20top%20dollar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody%20benefits%20when%20we%20all%20pool%20our%20listings%2C%20and%20we%20do%20so%20in%20a%20timely%20manner%2C%26quot%3B%20Saul%20Klein%2C%20a%20longtime%20real%20estate%20executive%20who's%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20San%20Diego%20Multiple%20Listing%20Service%2C%20previously%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20people%20are%20hurt%2C%20potentially%2C%20when%20we%20don't%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20become%20increasingly%20clear%20that%20the%20advocates%20for%20the%20open%20system%20are%20losing.%20Yes%2C%20NAR%20kept%20the%20clear%20cooperation%20rule%20in%20place%2C%20but%20it%20also%20introduced%20an%20option%20for%20privacy-conscious%20sellers%20to%20list%20on%20the%20MLS%20while%20delaying%20their%20listings%20from%20popping%20up%20on%20sites%20like%20Zillow%20or%20the%20landing%20pages%20for%20other%20brokerages.%20The%20idea%20is%20to%20give%20sellers%20more%20flexibility%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fshould-i-sell-my-house-now%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emarket%20their%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20they%20see%20fit%2C%20catering%20to%20those%20who%20may%20prefer%20to%20%26quot%3Bpremarket%26quot%3B%20their%20home%20before%20blasting%20it%20out%20widely.%20The%20move%20doesn't%20go%20nearly%20as%20far%20as%20Compass%20would%20have%20liked%2C%20but%20the%20company%20still%20frames%20this%20as%20a%20validation%20of%20its%20rallying%20cry%20for%20more%20seller%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20NAR%20introducing%20a%20new%20MLS%20policy%20to%20'expand%20choice%20for%20consumers%2C'%20they%20acknowledged%20the%20clear%20cooperation%20policy%20restricted%20home%20seller%20choice%2C%26quot%3B%20Reffkin%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BExpanding%20choice%20means%20that%20NAR%20is%20still%20not%20letting%20homeowners%20choose%20precisely%20how%20to%20market%20their%20homes%2C%20but%20this%20is%20a%20small%20step%20in%20the%20right%20direction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompass%20may%20not%20be%20totally%20happy%20with%20NAR's%20most%20recent%20decision%2C%20but%20the%20company%20has%20already%20succeeded%20in%20shaking%20up%20the%20real%20estate%20landscape.%20The%20brokerage%20has%20made%20plenty%20of%20hay%20by%20exploiting%20a%20glaring%20loophole%20in%20the%20clear%20cooperation%20rules.%20While%20an%20agent%20has%20to%20add%20the%20listing%20to%20the%20MLS%20database%20once%20they%20%3Cem%3Epublicly%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-agent-commissions-steering-hiding-homes-housing-market-lawsuits-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eput%20the%20home%20up%20for%20sale%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20rule%20allows%20agents%20to%20share%20new%20properties%20within%20their%20brokerages%20without%20adding%20them%20to%20the%20MLS.%20This%20method%2C%20which%20Compass%20dubbed%20the%20%26quot%3BPrivate%20Exclusive%26quot%3B%20route%2C%20essentially%20creates%20a%20walled%20garden%20with%20homes%20that%20can't%20be%20found%20anywhere%20else.%20Compass%20drives%20traffic%20to%20its%20website%2C%20collects%20a%20commission%20from%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20deal%2C%20and%20can%20lure%20both%20agents%20and%20clients%20by%20offering%20access%20to%20its%20inventory.%20Private%20exclusives%20have%20become%20a%20key%20strategy%20for%20the%20brokerage%20giant%3A%20Reffkin%20told%20analysts%20in%20February%20that%2035%25%20of%20the%20company's%20active%20listings%20nationwide%20were%20only%20available%20by%20working%20with%20a%20Compass%20agent%20or%20visiting%20Compass.com.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20just%20some%20self-serving%20maneuver%2C%20either%2C%20Compass%20execs%20argue.%20They%20say%20sellers%20benefit%20from%20spurning%20the%20MLS%20and%20marketing%20their%20homes%20within%20the%20safe%20confines%20of%20the%20Compass%20network.%20The%20MLS%20and%20search%20portals%20like%20Zillow%20show%20how%20long%20a%20house%20has%20been%20on%20the%20market%20and%20whether%20the%20price%20has%20been%20slashed%2C%20data%20points%20that%20buyers%20can%20use%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomebuyers-sellers-realtor-agent-commissions-saving-rule-changes-lawsuit-settlement-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eput%20pressure%20on%20homeowners%20in%20negotiations%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Compass%20website%20doesn't%20show%20price%20cuts%20or%20days%20on%20the%20market%2C%20theoretically%20allowing%20a%20seller%20to%20test%20their%20ideal%20price%20without%20any%20repercussions%20if%20they%20have%20to%20backtrack.%20And%20if%20they%20don't%20sell%20that%20way%2C%20they%20can%20always%20turn%20to%20the%20MLS%20and%20go%20the%20conventional%20route%20for%20maximum%20exposure.%20Compass%20likens%20this%20strategy%20to%20beta%20testing%20a%20product%20with%20a%20smaller%20audience%20before%20launch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20firmly%20believe%20that%20homeowners%20should%20have%20full%20control%20and%20flexibility%20in%20choosing%20how%20they%20market%20their%20home%2C%20period%2C%20full%20stop%2C%26quot%3B%20Ashton%20Alexander%2C%20the%20head%20of%20strategy%20at%20Compass%2C%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrian%20Boero%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%201000Watt%2C%20a%20brand%20and%20marketing%20agency%20for%20real%20estate%20companies%2C%20doesn't%20buy%20it.%20Compass%2C%20he%20says%2C%20is%20really%20after%20control.%20Under%20the%20existing%20rule%2C%20the%20company%20may%20be%20free%20to%20pursue%20its%20%26quot%3BPrivate%20Exclusives%26quot%3B%20strategy%2C%20but%20it%20can't%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20publicly%20market%20a%20home%20on%20its%20website%20without%20also%20contributing%20to%20the%20MLS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20want%20to%20make%20Compass.com%20a%20destination%20where%20they%20control%20the%20inventory%20publicly%2C%20and%20they%20want%20to%20have%20free%20rein%20to%20continue%20to%20expand%20their%20private%20listings%20program%2C%26quot%3B%20Boero%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BSo%20they%20didn't%20get%20what%20they%20wanted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompass%20is%20far%20from%20the%20only%20large%20brokerage%20to%20employ%20this%20kind%20of%20strategy%20%E2%80%94%20Coldwell%20Banker%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20has%20%26quot%3BExclusive%20Look%2C%26quot%3B%20Howard%20Hanna%20has%20%26quot%3BFind%20It%20First%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20one%20large%20Keller%20Williams%20franchise%2C%20KW%20Go%2C%20has%20dubbed%20its%20offering%20%26quot%3BPrivate%20Collection.%26quot%3B%20More%20companies%20have%20threatened%20to%20follow%20the%20lead%20and%20keep%20listings%20off%20the%20MLS%20if%20it%20helps%20them%20compete%20for%20agents%20and%20clients.%20The%20clear%20cooperation%20policy%20has%20always%20been%20tough%20to%20enforce%2C%20too%2C%20with%20the%20onus%20placed%20on%20local%20MLSes%20to%20keep%20agents%20in%20line.%20Some%20MLSes%2C%20fearing%20litigation%2C%20have%20already%20backed%20off%20enforcement%2C%20tacitly%20allowing%20agents%20to%20market%20homes%20however%20they%20like.%20This%20could%20enable%20private%20listing%20networks%20%E2%80%94%20groups%20of%20typically%20high-achieving%20agents%20from%20different%20brokerages%20who%20share%20off-MLS%20listings%20among%20each%20other%20%E2%80%94%20to%20flourish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENAR's%20decision%20to%20keep%20clear%20cooperation%20is%20a%20small%20victory%20for%20those%20who%20favor%20the%20status%20quo%2C%20but%20it%20will%20hardly%20end%20the%20practices%20fracturing%20the%20housing%20market.%20Compass%20hasn't%20ruled%20out%20the%20possibility%20of%20litigation%20over%20the%20rule%2C%20either.%20For%20now%2C%20the%20real%20estate%20industry%20is%20stuck%20in%20a%20sort%20of%20limbo.%20No%20one%20doubts%20that%20secret%20listings%20will%20continue%20to%20rise%2C%20but%20the%20fight%20over%20the%20clear%20cooperation%20policy%20isn't%20going%20anywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody%20lose