2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fis-shraddha-kapoors-x-account-hacked-concerned-fans-react-to-this-mysterious-tweet%2Farticleshow%2F119520546.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Malnutrition%3A%20The%20Domino%20Effect%20Of%20Undernourished%20Soil%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMeenakshi%2C%2025%2C%20sits%20on%20a%20porch%2C%20breastfeeding%20her%20youngest%20child.%20She%20tested%20positive%20for%20anaemia%20after%20her%20third%20child%20was%20born%20two%20years%20ago.%20Doctors%20recommended%20hospital%20admission%2C%20but%20the%20family%20could%20not%20afford%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeven%20years%20ago%2C%20Meenakshi%20was%20married%20into%20the%20Kumar%20family.%20Today%2C%20she%20is%20responsible%20for%20the%20food%20and%20nutritional%20needs%20of%20a%20family%20of%20eight%20-%20husband%2C%20in-laws%2C%20three%20children%20and%20a%20brother-in-law.%20The%20family%20eats%20what%20they%20grow.%20But%20the%20produce%20is%20often%20insufficient%20for%20the%20whole%20household.%20%26quot%3BAur%20kuch%20na%20ho%20to%20roti%20mirch%20kha%20leve%20(And%20when%20there%20is%20nothing%2C%20we%20eat%20roti%20bread%20with%20some%20chillies)%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Bijendra%20Kumar%2C%20Meenakshi's%20father-in-law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20having%20buffaloes%20at%20home%2C%20the%20children%20and%20adults%20do%20not%20consume%20milk.%20%26quot%3BIf%20everyone%20in%20the%20family%20starts%20drinking%20milk%2C%20what%20will%20we%20sell%20and%20earn%3F%26quot%3B%20asks%20Meenakshi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%2C%20we%20drink%20chaas%20(buttermilk).%20I%20add%20some%20water%20to%20the%20curd%2C%20increasing%20its%20quantity%3B%20blend%20and%20serve%20it%20to%20everyone%20as%20chaas.%20I%20cannot%20do%20the%20same%20to%20milk%2C%26quot%3B%20tells%20Meenakshi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStaples%20like%20pulses%20and%20cottage%20cheese%20(paneer)%2C%20generally%20packed%20with%20protein%2C%20vitamins%20and%20minerals%2C%20are%20absent%20from%20their%20diet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EGhana%20time%20ho%20gay%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20(It%20has%20been%20long%20since%20we%20last%20had%20pulses)%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20adds%20in%20a%20hushed%20tone%2C%20drawing%20a%20veil%20over%20her%20lean%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EPaneer%20to%20byah%20shaadi%20me%20banta%20hai%20tabhi%20khaate%20ha%3C%2Fem%3Ei%20(Cottage%20cheese%20is%20prepared%20on%20special%20occasions%20like%20weddings%20and%20that%20is%20when%20we%20get%20to%20taste%20it)%2C%26quot%3B%20adds%20Mr%20Kumar%20from%20behind.%20%26quot%3BI%20like%20to%20eat%20chicken%2C%20but%20where%20do%20we%20get%20it%20from%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeenakshi's%20nutritional%20status%20is%20likely%20to%20affect%20the%20health%20and%20well-being%20of%20her%20children.%20During%20pregnancy%2C%20anaemia%20has%20been%20associated%20with%20poor%20maternal%20and%20birth%20outcomes%2C%20including%20premature%20birth%2C%20low%20birth%20weight%20and%20maternal%20mortality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fvopbcuu8_woman-breastfeeding_625x300_25_March_25.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20stubbornly%20high%20malnutrition%20figures%20with%20one%20in%20five%20children%20under%20five%20reported%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bwasted%26quot%3B%20or%20too%20thin%20for%20their%20height.%20Nearly%20one-third%20of%20the%20children%20are%20stunted%20(too%20short%20for%20their%20age)%20and%20underweight.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20obesity%20among%20children%20has%20seen%20a%20jump%20from%202.1%20per%20cent%20to%203.4%20per%20cent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnaemia%2C%20a%20form%20of%20malnutrition%2C%20is%20also%20prevalent%20among%20children%20and%20women%20in%20India.%20Nearly%20seven%20in%2010%20children%20under%20five%20are%20anaemic.%20This%20has%20increased%20from%20six%20in%2010%20in%202015-16%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmohfw.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FNFHS-5_Phase-II_0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Family%20Health%20Survey-5%20(NFHS-5)%20for%202019-21%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Over%20half%20the%20women%20aged%2015-49%20are%20reported%20to%20have%20anaemia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20food%20we%20eat%20is%20not%20the%20only%20reason%20behind%20our%20nutritional%20status.%20Agricultural%20practices%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20part%20of%20our%20three-part%20series%2C%20we%20explore%20the%20impact%20of%20cultivating%20water-guzzling%20crops%20on%20nutrition.%20Read%20part%20one%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsip-by-sip-water-guzzling-crops-drain-indias-groundwater-7997301%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20part%20two%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdepleting-soil-health-the-price-of-growing-water-guzzling-crops-8004539%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20Reap%20What%20You%20Sow%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnhealthy%20soil%20produces%20unhealthy%20crops%2C%20which%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20leave%20us%20unhealthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20how%20Dr%20Rajiv%20Tandon%2C%20Consultant%20Paediatrician%20and%20Executive%20Director%2C%20The%20Health%20Continuum%2C%20explains%20the%20domino%20effect%20of%20soil%20health%20on%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BSoil%20health%20manifests%20directly%20with%20micronutrient%20deficiencies%20within%20the%20food%20items%20and%20eventually%20leads%20to%20the%20same%20low%20levels%20of%20minerals%20and%20vitamins%20in%20the%20people%20consuming%20that%20particular%20food%20item.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEating%20food%20grown%20in%20nutritionally%20deficient%20soils%20can%20lead%20to%20malnutrition%20which%20could%20manifest%20as%20long-term%20stunting%2C%20wasting%2C%20underweight%2C%20anaemia%2C%20among%20other%20health%20issues%2C%20Dr%20Tandon%20explains.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20is%20reflected%20in%20both%20cognitive%20and%20productive%20outcomes%20of%20human%20beings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnews-room%2Ffact-sheets%2Fdetail%2Fmalnutrition%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20Health%20Organisation%20(WHO)%20defines%20malnutrition%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20deficiencies%2C%20excesses%2C%20or%20imbalances%20in%20a%20person's%20energy%20and%2For%20nutrient%20intake.%20Undernutrition%20(wasting%2C%20stunting%20and%20underweight)%2C%20micronutrient%20deficiencies%20or%20excesses%2C%20overweight%2C%20obesity%2C%20and%20diet-related%20non-communicable%20diseases%20are%20all%20forms%20of%20malnutrition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20soil%20health%20is%20critical%20for%20nutrient-rich%20plants%2C%20several%20other%20factors%20impact%20nutritional%20outcomes%2C%20such%20as%20poverty%20levels%20and%20access%20to%20basics%20like%20clean%20water%20and%20healthcare.%20An%20analysis%20of%20the%20nutritional%20status%20of%20children%20and%20women%20in%20states%20growing%20water-intensive%20and%20non-water-intensive%20crops%20provides%20a%20much%20more%20nuanced%20portrait.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChild%20malnutrition%20figures%20are%20slightly%20higher%20in%20states%20growing%20non-water-intensive%20crops%2C%20like%20Jharkhand%2C%20Odisha%2C%20and%20Tripura%2C%20than%20in%20the%20top%20three%20states%20growing%20water-intensive%20crops%20-%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Gujarat%20and%20Rajasthan%20-%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fspreadsheets%2Fd%2F15zazdnJi1h8bBHEnnzXm0T4iyq1Fwi9NkA94qAARKdo%2Fedit%3Fgid%3D2046871873%23gid%3D2046871873%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENFHS-5%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20one%20reason%20why%20water-intensive%20crop-growing%20states%20may%20have%20comparatively%20better%20health%20outcomes%20despite%20equally%20bad%20soil%20health%2C%20Ashok%20Kumar%2C%20an%20agronomist%20at%20FAO%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BJharkhand%2C%20Odisha%2C%20and%20Tripura%20have%20significantly%20higher%20populations%20of%20scheduled%20tribes.%20Tribes%20follow%20their%20traditional%20agriculture%20practices%20which%20provide%20lower%20production%20and%20low%20income.%20They%20have%20limited%20access%20to%20sanitation%20and%20healthcare%2C%20which%20leads%20to%20poor%20health%20negatively%20affecting%20nutritional%20status%20resulting%20in%20stunted%2C%20wasted%20and%20underweight%20children.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Gujarat%20and%20Rajasthan%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fstatistics%2F1027998%2Findia-per-capita-income-by-state%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigher%20per%20capita%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20states%20that%20primarily%20grow%20non-water-intensive%20crops.%20More%20income%20gives%20people%20the%20financial%20freedom%20to%20purchase%20better%20food%2C%20which%20may%20or%20may%20not%20be%20grown%20locally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20average%2C%20more%20women%20were%20reported%20to%20have%20lower%20body%20mass%20index%20(BMI)%20-%20an%20indicator%20of%20malnourishment%20-%20in%20the%20top%20three%20states%20growing%20non-water-intensive%20crops.%20The%20top%20three%20states%20primarily%20growing%20water-intensive%20food%20crops%20have%20a%20higher%20percentage%20of%20obese%20or%20overweight%20women%2C%20again%20a%20parameter%20of%20malnourishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FkFcEb%2F12%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22More%20malnutrition%20in%20states%20primarily%20growing%20non-thirsty%20crops%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22609%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20average%2C%20one%20in%20five%20women%20in%20the%20top%20states%20growing%20water-intensive%20non-staple%20food%20crops%20-%20Goa%2C%20Gujarat%20and%20Rajasthan%20-%20have%20low%20BMI%2C%20a%20slightly%20higher%20rate%20than%20women%20in%20states%20growing%20water-intensive%20staple%20food%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20nearly%20one%20in%20three%20women%20are%20obese%20or%20overweight%20-%20also%20a%20sign%20of%20malnourishment%20in%20the%20top%20states%20growing%20water-intensive%20staple%20food%20crops%20-%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20Punjab.%20This%20is%20slightly%20(8.8%20percentage%20points)%20higher%20than%20the%20level%20of%20obese%20women%20in%20top%20states%20growing%20water-intensive%20non-staple%20food%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fspreadsheets%2Fd%2F15zazdnJi1h8bBHEnnzXm0T4iyq1Fwi9NkA94qAARKdo%2Fedit%3Fgid%3D266014967%23gid%3D266014967%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENFHS-5%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20a%20higher%20prevalence%20of%20child%20anaemia%20in%20the%20top%20three%20states%20growing%20water-intensive%20crops%2C%20while%20anaemia%20among%20women%20was%20more%20prevalent%20in%20the%20top%20three%20states%20cultivating%20non-water-intensive%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FYKyXL%2F6%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Higher%20percentage%20of%20children%20under%20five%20with%20anaemia%20in%20states%20primarily%20growing%20water-intensive%20crops%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22339%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20average%2C%20two%20out%20of%20three%20children%20under%20the%20age%20of%20five%20had%20anemia%20in%20both%20the%20top%20three%20staple%20food%20growing%20states%20and%20non-staple%20food%20growing%20states.%20This%20is%20at%20par%20with%20the%20national%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnaemia%20in%20mothers%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC11901893%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DChildren%2520born%2520to%2520anemic%2520mothers%2520had%252089%2525%2520higher%2520odds%2520of%2C%252C%2520child%252C%2520and%2520household%2520characteristics.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecan%20be%20passed%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20their%20children%2C%20which%20means%20Meenakshi's%20children%20are%20prone%20to%20becoming%20victims%20of%20an%20intergenerational%20cycle%20of%20anaemia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20children%2C%20anaemia%20can%20also%20lead%20to%20poor%20cognitive%20and%20motor%20development%2C%20states%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnews-room%2Ffact-sheets%2Fdetail%2Fanaemia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWHO%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDietary%20choices%20impact%20nutritional%20outcomes%20as%20well%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frontiersin.org%2Fjournals%2Fsustainable-food-systems%2Farticles%2F10.3389%2Ffsufs.2025.1490050%2Ffull%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20widespread%20inadequate%20protein%20consumption%20despite%20access%20to%20protein-rich%20foods%20such%20as%20legumes%2C%20dairy%2C%20meat%20and%20eggs.%20The%20results%20show%20that%20%26quot%3Boften%20most%20households%20did%20not%20intentionally%20choose%20protein-rich%20foods%2C%20resulting%20in%20cereals%20becoming%20the%20primary%20source%20of%20protein%20and%20contributing%2063-73%20per%20cent%20of%20total%20protein%20intake%20across%20the%20various%20districts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20income%20analysis%20revealed%20that%20protein%20deficiency%20was%20rampant%20across%20seven%20in%2010%20households%2C%20regardless%20of%20their%20economic%20condition.%20Protein%20consumption%20is%20influenced%20by%20education%2C%20particularly%20of%20women's%2C%20and%20social%2C%20economic%20and%20cultural%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithout%20targeted%20efforts%20to%20promote%20diverse%20diets%20and%20educate%20communities%20on%20the%20importance%20of%20protein%2C%20malnutrition%20will%20persist%2C%26quot%3B%20noted%20Dr%20Shalander%20Kumar%2C%20the%20study's%20lead%20researcher%20and%20Deputy%20Global%20Research%20Program%20Director%20of%20the%20Enabling%20Systems%20Transformation%20Program%20at%20ICRISAT%2C%20in%20an%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpressroom.icrisat.org%2Fhidden-hunger-protein-deficiency-plagues-rural-india-despite-availability-and-affordability%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eofficial%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAgroecology%20is%20the%20way%20forward%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDevinder%20Sharma%2C%20a%20food%20policy%20expert%2C%20believes%20transitioning%20to%20agroecology%20will%20conserve%20water%20and%20prevent%20soil%20degradation%20and%20nutrition%20depletion.%20Agroecology%20is%20an%20ecological%20approach%20to%20agriculture%20that%20involves%20the%20sustainable%20use%20of%20natural%20resources.%20It%20seeks%20to%20optimise%20the%20interaction%20between%20plants%2C%20animals%2C%20humans%2C%20and%20the%20environment%20while%20ensuring%20an%20equitable%20food%20system.%20This%20includes%20diversification-agroforestry%2C%20intercropping%2C%20crop%20rotation%20-%20and%20sustainable%20land%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20if%20Meenakshi's%20family%20starts%20using%20farmyard%20manure%20(a%20mix%20of%20plant%20and%20animal%20waste)%2C%20they%20can%20increase%20soil%20fertility%20and%20produce%20quality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCrop%20rotation%20means%20growing%20rice%20or%20wheat%20in%20one%20season%20and%20pulses%20and%20legumes%20in%20another.%20This%20can%20help%20balance%20nitrogen%20availability%20in%20the%20soil.%20Coupled%20with%20no-tilling%2C%20it%20can%20improve%20soil%20microbes%2C%26quot%3B%20explained%20Mr%20Kumar%20from%20FAO.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Kumar%20suggested%20developing%20drought-resistant%20and%20soil-friendly%20crop%20varieties%20to%20improve%20resilience%20to%20changing%20environmental%20conditions.%20Implementing%20precision%20agriculture%20techniques%20can%20optimise%20resource%20use%20and%20reduce%20environmental%20impact.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20food%20policy%20expert%20also%20recommended%20examining%20the%20economics%20of%20agriculture%20and%20suggests%20incentivising%20farmers%20to%20grow%20crops%20that%20require%20less%20material%2C%20protect%20soil%2C%20and%20retain%20nutrition.%20%26quot%3BA%20farmer%20will%20diversify%20or%20switch%20to%20any%20other%20crop%20only%20when%20they%20get%20a%20similar%20price.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChanging%20age-old%20practices%20and%20beliefs%20also%20remains%20a%20major%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20farmers%20like%20Bijendra%20Kumar%20believe%20that%20water%20sprinkling%20is%20not%20sufficient%20as%20the%20water%20does%20not%20reach%20the%20plants'%20roots.%20Already%20knee%20deep%20in%20debt%2C%20he%20does%20not%20have%20more%20money%20to%20invest%20in%20another%20technique.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2F2q6isn38_farmer-rajasthan_625x300_25_March_25.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20experts%2C%20however%2C%20think%20that%20soon%2C%20farmers%20may%20not%20have%20a%20choice%20but%20to%20shift%20to%20other%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Yadav%20believes%20that%20groundwater%20depletion%20will%20eventually%20push%20farmers%20to%20non-water-intensive%20crops%20or%20water-saving%20methods%2C%20as%20they%20will%20be%20left%20with%20no%20other%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20Meenakshi%20is%20concerned%2C%20she%20has%20accepted%20malnutrition%20as%20her%20fate%20and%20does%20not%20think%20or%20worry%20about%20the%20future.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20will%20you%20think%20when%20there%20is%20nothing%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMethodology%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20data%20story%20looks%20at%20the%20impact%20of%20growing%20water-intensive%20crops%20on%20groundwater%2C%20soil%20health%20and%20human%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20begin%20with%2C%20the%20author%20looked%20at%20the%20%26quot%3BMekonnen%2C%20M.M.%20and%20Hoekstra%2C%20A.Y.%20(2010)%20The%20green%2C%20blue%20and%20grey%20water%20footprint%20of%20crops%20and%20derived%20crop%20products%26quot%3B%20report%20to%20identify%20water-intensive%20crops%20in%20states%20across%20India.%20The%20author%20considered%20only%20blue%20water%20footprint%20data%20to%20know%20how%20much%20groundwater%20is%20being%20used%20to%20irrigate%20a%20crop%2C%20in%20a%20state.%20If%20a%20state%20uses%20more%20blue%20water%20than%20the%20national%20average%20to%20grow%20a%20certain%20crop%2C%20then%20the%20author%20considered%20the%20crop%20%26quot%3Bwater-intensive%26quot%3B%20in%20that%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20author%20also%20looked%20at%20the%20%26quot%3BArea%2C%20Production%20%26amp%3B%20Yield%20-%20Reports%26quot%3B%20from%202013-2023%20to%20calculate%20the%20proportion%20of%20area%20under%20cultivation%20of%20water-intensive%20or%20non-water-intensive%20crops%20in%20each%20state.%20The%20area%2C%20production%20and%20yield%20reports%20were%20taken%20from%20the%20official%20website%20of%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Economics%20and%20Statistics%2C%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%20and%20Farmers%20Welfare%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Agriculture%20%26amp%3B%20Farmers%20Welfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20this%20methodology%2C%20the%20author%20identified%20three%20states%20with%20the%20highest%20proportion%20of%20area%20under%20cultivation%20for%20water-intensive%20crops%20and%20three%20states%20with%20the%20highest%20proportion%20of%20area%20under%20cultivation%20for%20non-water-intensive%20crops.%20They%20then%20looked%20at%20Soil%20Health%20Card%20data%20(2023-24)%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Agriculture%20and%20Farmers%20Welfare.%20They%20focused%20on%20the%20status%20of%20macronutrients%20(N%2C%20P%2C%20K)%20and%20micronutrients%20(S%2C%20Fe%2C%20Zn)%20in%20the%20soil%20to%20see%20if%20the%20soil%20in%20states%20growing%20water-intensive%20crops%20is%20more%20deficient%20in%20essential%20nutrients.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20author%20also%20looked%20at%20the%20National%20Family%20Health%20Survey%20(NFHS-5)%20data%20specifically%20for%20the%20six%20states%20and%20analysed%20data%20for%20key%20health%20indicators%20-%20malnutrition%20and%20anaemia%20among%20children%20under%20five%20and%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20supporting%20data%20and%20analysis%20can%20be%20accessed%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fspreadsheets%2Fd%2F1Fl5uKcofimHXMaNVLzXYDjf0JJrwV5vkkA6uFz0lTKA%2Fedit%3Fgid%3D0%23gid%3D0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20author%20travelled%20to%20Alwar%20district%20in%20Rajasthan%20and%20met%20farmers%20in%20different%20villages%20to%20understand%20their%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Reporting%20for%20this%20story%20was%20supported%20by%20the%20Environmental%20Data%20Journalism%20Academy-%20a%20program%20of%20Internews'%20Earth%20Journalism%20Network%20and%20Thibi.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742969340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fuatlglf8_farmer-kitchen-garden_625x300_25_March_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmalnutrition-the-domino-effect-of-undernourished-soil-8010023%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%